 the Faculty Handbook and University administration</p><p>Researches instructional strategies to inform continuous improvement in the student experience</p><p>Uses a variety of communication methods to support students learning needs.</p><p>Implements instructional strategies appropriate for the learner and content, differentiating instruction to meet diverse learner needs. Uses student data to remediate and scaffold development</p><p>As needed, engages with appropriate administrators to support the student experience and to ensure student needs are being addressed</p><p>Effectively uses a mentor/coach approach to build productive educational relationships with students.</p><p>Applies flexibility and creativity in meeting student needs, ensuring availability to students as needed, based on the learning environment and according to University policy and instructional standards</p><p>Engages in professional development activities to maintain currency in educational research, trends and best practices</p><p>Maintains active involvement in academic discipline, such as participation in professional organizations, academic conferences, and/or community service</p><p>Engages in regular self-assessment and reflection to increase the quality of instruction.</p><p>Performs other duties as assigned</p><p>Occasional travel may be required</p><p>Qualifications</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Basic Qualifications</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Doctorate Degree in Nursing or related field REQUIRED from a nationally accredited program.</p><p>Master&#39;s Degree in Nursing REQUIRED</p><p>An active unencumbered license to practice as a Registered Nurse in Colorado or compact state</p><p>At least three (3) years of continuous full-time direct care experience working in the designated nursing area of Medical-Surgical within the last five (5) years.</p><p>At least one (1) year of teaching Registered Nursing and or the completion of a post-baccalaureate course in teaching Registered Nursing</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Additional Qualifications</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Experience with qualitative and quantitative research</p><p>Experience teaching diverse adult learner populations</p><p>Able to demonstrate a high level of problem solving and decision making abilities to respond to student issues and concerns, evaluate students for potential barriers to retention, assess student work and abilities and to facilitate the learning experience.</p><p>Able to be self-motivated and have proven the ability to work independently managing multiple priorities and tasks for to deliver required results efficiently and effectively.</p><p>Able to communicate effectively with diverse constituencies, including students, faculty, employees, and external parties leveraging oral, written, and interpersonal communication skills</p><p>Ability to convey a professional image, as well as effectively represent the organization as appropriate in its relationship with the community</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>#LI-MD1</p><p>#SONHOTJOBS</p><p>Options</p><br /><br /><div style="text-align:left;padding-bottom: 20px;"><a href="/frca-apply/bjl1gu" id="ApplyBottomLink" target="_blank" class="bigBlueButtonLink" rel="nofollow" onclick="javascript:setTimeout(&quot;window.location.href = &#39;/post-resume?jid=bjl1gu&#39;;&quot;,1500); return true;">Go to apply&nbsp;<img src="/Images/applyarrow.png" height="21x;" width="16px;" alt="" /></a></div></div></div></div><div style="background-color: #fcfcfc; max-width: 400px;" class="sideBar"><div style="text-align:left; vertical-align:top; padding-left:5px;"><h4 style="padding-bottom:7px;">Similar Jobs</h4><p style="padding-bottom:4px;"><a href="/job/bjn2td/instructor-instructional-lone-tree-co" rel="nofollow" onclick="ga(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;Links&#39;, &#39;JobToJob&#39;, &#39;0&#39;);">Nursing Instructor Faculty, Pediatrics</a><br/><span style="font-size:small" class="colorLocation">Lone Tree, CO</span><s